# System Architecture Map — Integration Hub

This rule gives the agent a “map” of the platform so it implements features in the correct place, with correct boundaries, and correct data flow.

## 1) Product boundaries (never blur these)

### Admin Plane (Control Plane)
- Purpose: governance + onboarding + approvals + visibility (with PHI gating)
- Writes: control_plane.* (configs) and audit events (governed)
- Reads: control_plane.*, data_plane.* (summaries), usage.* (aggregates), audit.* (redacted by default)

### Vendor Plane
- Purpose: vendor configuration + vendor-safe views (no other vendors’ data)
- Identity: derived only from JWT claim `bcpAuth`
- Never exposes: other vendors’ config or any admin-only controls

### Runtime Plane (Data Plane)
- Purpose: execute + ai/execute
- Must be stable, fast, and fail-open on ancillary systems (usage emission, AI formatter calls, etc.)
- Identity: derived only from JWT claim `bcpAuth`
- Never trusts: request body for source vendor identity

## 2) Core subsystems and “where logic lives”

### Canonical Data Model + Contracts
- Source of truth: control_plane.operations + control_plane.operation_contracts
- Vendor override: control_plane.vendor_operation_contracts (only when vendor chooses override)
- Runtime must validate requests against canonical contract unless vendor override is active

### Allowlist / Access Rules
- Source of truth: control_plane.vendor_operation_allowlist
- Current policy: explicit allowlist pairs (no wildcard `*`)
- UI should support bulk creation (multi-source + multi-target)

### Endpoints + Outbound Auth
- Outbound endpoint: control_plane.vendor_endpoints
- Endpoint auth linkage: by FK (whatever schema enforces today)
- Outbound auth types supported: API_KEY_HEADER, API_KEY_QUERY, BASIC, BEARER, JWT, MTLS
- Endpoint verification must be SSRF-safe and secrets-redacted

### Execution Runtime
- Entry points: /v1/execute, /v1/ai/execute
- Must enforce: JWT → vendor identity → allowlist → contract validation → routing → audit
- Must emit: audit lifecycle events and (if enabled) usage events
- Must not store PHI in logs; only redacted/audited paths can expose sensitive data

### AI Formatter
- Triggered only when feature gate + op mode + request flag allow it
- Deterministic precedence everywhere: GLOBAL_GATE -> OP_MODE -> REQUEST_FLAG -> FORMATTER_CALL
- AI failure never changes execute outcome; only aiFormatter metadata changes

### Replay Console
- Admin-only capability with strict audit trail
- Uses data_plane transactions + audit events; never bypasses allowlist rules
- Must preserve idempotency semantics

### Flow Builder
- Admin governance tool to configure operations, allowlist, endpoints, mappings, and approvals
- Must operate only via control plane APIs and change request workflow where required

### Usage & Billing (Vendor-focused)
- Identity: vendor is always `bcpAuth`
- Event emission: fail-open (execution must still succeed)
- No PHI: usage tables must not include payload/request/response bodies

### PHI / Privacy
- Default: redact request/response payloads everywhere
- Expand requires: PHI-approved group + explicit reason + auto-timeout
- Always redact secrets even in PHI mode
- Emit audit events when PHI view is enabled and used

## 3) “Routing rules” for implementation (avoid wrong placement)

When the change affects:
- auth / identity / scopes / audiences → update bcpAuth + gateway config + tests
- governance / onboarding / approvals → update Admin Plane endpoints + UI + rules
- runtime behavior (execute / ai/execute) → update Runtime Plane handlers + contract + allowlist + audit tests
- endpoint auth types → update endpoint resolver + verifier + admin UX help panels
- seed/demo → update seed_local.py AND ensure migrations are head

## 4) Non-negotiable invariants
- Vendor A cannot read Vendor B’s config or data (including “debug” views)
- Source vendor identity is only from JWT `bcpAuth`
- Contract validation is enforced before routing
- Allowlist is enforced before routing
- PHI is redacted by default; expanded only with approval + audit trail
- AI formatter never becomes required for runtime success

## 5) Agent expectations
For any feature request:
- Identify impacted subsystems above
- Implement end-to-end wiring (DB → backend → UI → tests → rules)
- Provide a summary of files touched and how the feature obeys invariants